[SN]TITLE[SN]
Six-mile A470 queue after accident

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A six-mile queue formed on the A470 on the southern approach towards Cardiff following an accident on Tuesday morning.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Two people were injured after two cars collided near the Upper Boat interchange just before 07:00 GMT.
The accident initially closed the main carriageway but after it was cleared a van broke down near the A4054 interchange.
One of the southbound lanes was blocked at the scene.
